## Validation Checklist

Before marking implementation complete, verify:

- [ ] Visual output matches Figma screenshot (1:1 parity)
- [ ] All assets from Figma are properly integrated (no placeholders)
- [ ] Reused existing shadcn/ui components where applicable
- [ ] Used `cn()` utility for conditional classes
- [ ] Followed project's TypeScript conventions
- [ ] Added unit tests (Vitest) for business logic
- [ ] Added E2E tests (Playwright) if UI flow is affected
- [ ] Ran `npm run lint` and `npm run typecheck` with zero errors
- [ ] Ran `npm run test:coverage` with >90% coverage
- [ ] Responsive design works across breakpoints
- [ ] Accessibility requirements met (WCAG compliance)

---

## Common Pitfalls to Avoid

- ❌ Skipping `get_design_context` or `get_screenshot`
- ❌ Creating new components when shadcn/ui equivalents exist
- ❌ Hardcoding colors/spacing instead of using Tailwind tokens
- ❌ Using inline styles instead of Tailwind classes
- ❌ Adding new icon libraries instead of using Figma assets
- ❌ Creating placeholders when localhost sources are available
- ❌ Ignoring responsive design considerations
- ❌ Not testing the implementation against the Figma screenshot
- ❌ Forgetting to run quality checks (`lint`, `typecheck`, `test`)

---

## Example Workflow

```bash
# 1. Get design context from Figma node
> Use MCP: get_design_context with node URL

# 2. Get visual reference
> Use MCP: get_screenshot with node URL

# 3. Download assets if needed
> Use MCP asset endpoint for images/icons

# 4. Implement using existing components
> Check src/components/ui/ for shadcn components
> Reuse existing components, use cn() utility

# 5. Run quality checks
npm run lint && npm run typecheck && npm run test:coverage

# 6. Validate against Figma
> Compare implementation with get_screenshot output
```
